00:00:00.510 --> 00:00:03.080
&gt;&gt; Hello and welcome to this step-by-step
video

00:00:03.080 --> 00:00:06.090
in which we will show you how to use the power
options

00:00:06.090 --> 00:00:09.290
on the Galaxy Gear 2 to your Galaxy device.

00:00:09.290 --> 00:00:14.430
Please note: Your first need to connect you
Galaxy Gear 2 to your Galaxy device.

00:00:14.430 --> 00:00:18.760
If you have not already done so,
please watch our video, 'How to connect your

00:00:18.760 --> 00:00:24.820
Galaxy Gear 2 and Samsung Galaxy device.'
Apart from turning the device on,

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:28.410
you can use the power button to perform these
other functions.

00:00:28.410 --> 00:00:33.250
1. Press and hold to turn the device on or
off.

00:00:33.250 --> 00:00:40.190
2. Briefly press to return to the clock screen.
3. Press to lock the device on the Clock screen.

00:00:40.190 --> 00:00:44.660
The device goes into lock mode when the touch
screen turns off.

00:00:44.660 --> 00:00:49.519
Press again to unlock the device.
4. Press and hold for at least 7 seconds to

00:00:49.519 --> 00:00:52.239
reset the Gear.

00:00:52.239 --> 00:00:57.659
Using the Gear manager app on the Galaxy S5
it's possible to set up the power button to

00:00:57.659 --> 00:01:01.399
launch an application by pressing the power
button twice.

00:01:01.399 --> 00:01:07.960
To do this tap apps on the home screen.
Then select the Gear manager app.

00:01:07.960 --> 00:01:15.940
In the Gear manager app, select settings.
Then select, 'Double pressing the home key'.

00:01:15.940 --> 00:01:20.610
A list of options will be displayed.
In this example we have selected the gallery

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:25.610
app.
The s5 and Gear 2 will be updated with your

00:01:25.610 --> 00:01:26.750
choice.

00:01:26.750 --> 00:01:32.240
Pressing the power home button twice will
launch the gallery app on the Gear 2 device.

00:01:32.240 --> 00:01:35.560
It is also possible to launch the safety assistance
feature,

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:39.320
by pressing the power button three times in
brief succession.

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:45.920
In the Gear manager app on the S5, tap settings,
then send help message.

00:01:45.920 --> 00:01:49.570
Then drag the safety assistance switch to
the right.

00:01:49.570 --> 00:01:54.560
After agreeing with the terms and conditions,
a popup will be displayed asking you to set

00:01:54.560 --> 00:02:00.380
up an emergency contact.
Tap OK.

00:02:00.380 --> 00:02:06.990
Now tap the plus icon to add a contact.
A popup will appear asking you to choose between

00:02:06.990 --> 00:02:13.670
creating or selecting a contact.
Here we are going to create a contact.

00:02:13.670 --> 00:02:17.849
Add the name and number of the person you
wish to receive the message.

00:02:17.849 --> 00:02:24.340
Then tap save.
Please follow this advice to get the best

00:02:24.340 --> 00:02:30.099
from your Galaxy Gear device.
Humidity and liquids may damage your device.

00:02:30.099 --> 00:02:32.760
Keep your device dry.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:37.549
Do not use a screen protector - This causes
sensor malfunctions.

00:02:37.549 --> 00:02:42.750
Do not allow water to contact the touch screen.
The touch screen may malfunction in humid

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:45.670
conditions or when exposed to water.

00:02:45.670 --> 00:02:49.129
That's it!
You've just learned how to use the power button

00:02:49.129 --> 00:02:54.239
option on the Galaxy Gear 2 device.

